RAILROAD COMMISSION OF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA
October 3, 1929.
Case 1433.
Mr.
Joseph J.
Phillips,
Chief Right of Way Agent,
City and County of San Francisco,
San Francisco,
Calif.
Dear Sir:
Responsive to your request October first, there is
enclosed herewith pamphlet copy of our Decision No. 8960 in
Application No. 6390, đecided May 12, 1921, which decision re-
quired the Southern Pacific Company to readjust its switching
rates between points within San Francisco, including South San
Francisco. The decument is the writer's desk copy, and when it
has served your purpose, would be pleased to have you return it
to w. P. Geary.
Yours very truly,
RAILROAD COMMISSION OF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA
By
SHe Mathewson
H. G. Mathewson, Secretary.

properties.sfomuseum:description: Correspondence from H. G. Mathewson, Secretary of Railroad Commission of the State of California, to Joseph J. Phillips, Chief Right of Way Agent, City and County of San Francisco, dated October 3, 1929, informing of Decision No. 8960 in Application No. 6390, decided May 12, 1921, requiring Southern Pacific Company to readjust switching rates between points in San Francisco and South San Francisco; typewritten page with handwritten notations.
